history.content:
We’re looking for interested undergrads/grads who have a Python background and some understanding of AI/ML, specifically RL, to help out with a research project. The project entails downloading and analyzing a dataset of 5M+ games of Dominion (https://dominion.games/), and training a reinforcement learning agent to beat pre existing baselines. 


We have progressed quite far into this project (https://github.com/aronsar/domray), and have already submitted a paper and received useful feedback for changes to make that will result in acceptance at a future conference. Please send your resume to aronsar@gmail.com to apply.

note: this project is not affiliated with Berkeley; I simply am a student at Berkeley who is apart of the project
history.subject: Student Research Opportunity in RL
